description: {"blocks":[{"key":"82n4q","text":"A transmission electron microscope (TEM) enables the magnification and visualisation of cell and tissue ultrastructure that cannot otherwise be resolved using a light microscope. In transmission electron microscopy, a high energy electron beam generated from an electron gun is focused by electromagnetic lenses onto an ultrathin section of plastic embedded specimen. Electrons are transmitted through the specimen onto a fluorescent screen based on sample density, and an image is acquired by a digital camera. Here, a protocol for preparing tissue specimens for TEM ultrastructural analysis is described. A tissue specimen is fixed, dehydrated and infiltrated with resin. The resin is then polymerised, and embedded tissue sectioned using an ultramicrotome. Ultrathin sections are contrasted with heavy metals prior to imaging using a TEM. Options for faster processing using a Microwave processor are described for relevant steps.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"1283o","text":"Place the tissue pieces in 5 ml tubes, 15 ml Falcon® tubes or a well-plate containing 2% paraformaldehyde, 2.5% glutaraldehyde in 0.1M cacodylate buffer and fix overnight at 4 degrees Celsius or for 2-4 hours at room temperature, on a rotor. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"2h9se","text":"For Steps 6-19, do not proceed if samples float following ethanol, acetone or Epon resin infiltration. {"blocks":[{"key":"4j0tr","text":"Dehydrate in 70% ethanol in MilliQ water for 1 hour at room temperature, agitating. Tissue can be left at 4 degrees Celsius, overnight if necessary.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"b1gp2","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"4jlot","text":"Biowave settings: 40 seconds, 150W, No vacuum.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"ds4je","text":"Dehydrate in 90% ethanol in MilliQ water for 1 hour at room temperature, agitating.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"52asi","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"8kvvn","text":"Biowave settings: 40 seconds, 150W, No vacuum.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"2t9f","text":"Dehydrate in 95% ethanol in MilliQ water for 1 hour at room temperature, agitating.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"d28ld","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"57m04","text":"Biowave settings: 40 seconds, 150W, No vacuum.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"d2pfr","text":"Dehydrate in 100% ethanol for 1 hour at room temperature, agitating.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"e6lo","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"15pjd","text":"Biowave settings: 40 seconds, 150W, No vacuum.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"2s9db","text":"Dehydrate in 100% anhydrous ethanol for 1 hour at room temperature, agitating. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"frbqu","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"2m99l","text":"Biowave settings: 40 seconds, 150W, No vacuum.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"bh0l2","text":"Dehydrate in 100% acetone for 1 hour at room temperature, agitating.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"fj00d","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"335ec","text":"Biowave settings: 40 seconds, 150W, No vacuum.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"2gko2","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"934ob","text":"Propylene oxide can be used as an alternative to acetone (Steps 13-17), but is extremely toxic and may dehydrate samples too intensively, causing ultrastructural damage. {"blocks":[{"key":"aibda","text":"Dehydrate in 100% anhydrous acetone for 1 hour at room temperature, agitating. Type 3Å molecular sieves can be added to the acetone stock solution to dehydrate the solvent prior to use. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"cch2i","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"3cc5i","text":"Biowave settings: 40 seconds, 150W, No vacuum.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"2covl","text":"Optionally Infiltrate with 100% anhydrous acetone : epon resin (3 : 1 ratio) overnight at room temperature, agitating. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"dnpvi","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"3btb2","text":"Biowave settings: 3 minutes, 250W, Vacuum on.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"bpp09","text":"Infiltrate with 100% anhydrous acetone : epon resin (1 : 1 ratio) for 6 hours at room temperature, agitating. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"ddfad","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"601rd","text":"Biowave settings: 3 minutes, 250W, Vacuum on.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"9vhhb","text":"Infiltrate with 100% anhydrous acetone : epon resin (1 : 3 ratio) overnight at room temperature, agitating.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"c14nc","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"487ti","text":"Biowave settings: 3 minutes, 250W, Vacuum on. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"eva84","text":"Infiltrate with 100% epon resin for 6 hours at room temperature, agitating.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"50s1v","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"8mtg8","text":"Biowave settings: 3 minutes, 250W, Vacuum on.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"5bskq","text":"Infiltrate with 100% epon resin overnight at room temperature, agitating.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"ebc0m","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"3uvbp","text":"Biowave settings: 3 minutes, 250W, Vacuum on.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"c5sp6","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"23acj","text":"Residual acetone can adversely impact resin infiltration and polymerisation. {"blocks":[{"key":"1veop","text":"Transfer samples to labelled plastic embedding moulds, flat bottom BEEM® capsules or standard tip BEEM® capsules containing 100% epon resin. {"blocks":[{"key":"cn8m2","text":"Mount the resin-embedded tissue block in an ultramicrotome chuck, and secure the chuck to a stereo microscope fitted with a chuck mount. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"2ur8i","text":"Transfer the chuck and resin-embedded tissue block to a Leica UC7 ultramicrotome and secure in place. Trim the front surface of the block face until a full tissue face has been obtained. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"5r4b5","text":"To check the region of interest:  ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"2sap3","text":"Cut 500 nm semi thin sections at a speed of 1 mm/sec using a Leica UC7 ultramicrotome and 45 degree glass knife  fitted with a filtered water-filled boat or suitable diamond knife. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"6ncjo","text":"Retrieve sections with an eyelash or Dalmatian hair mounted on a wooden stick and float sections in a drop of MilliQ water on a slide before drying on a mini hot plate. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"cp1nc","text":"Stain sections with Toluidine blue solution for 10-20 seconds on a mini hot plate before rinsing with MilliQ water and drying on a mini hot plate.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"dhgvf","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"661rt","text":"Toluidine blue stains nucleic acids and proteins, enhancing structural detail of semi thin tissue sections.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"cf12s","text":"Observe sections with a wide-field light microscope. If the region of interest has not been obtained, trim deeper and repeat Step 23. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"3cgvr","text":"Cut 90 nm gold coloured ultrathin sections at 1 mm/sec using a Leica UC7 ultramicrotome and a Diatome 45 degree angle ultra wet diamond knife. Spread the sections using a Max Wax heat pen to remove wrinkles. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"5egg","text":"Pick up sections on 50-200 mesh copper or palladium-coated copper grids using an eyelash or Dalmatian hair mounted on a wooden stick. Store grids in an enclosed grid box until use.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"6us0n","text":"Place a sheet of parafilm on a clean flat bench or glass board using a small amount of water underneath to keep the film flat. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"e8qdb","text":"For the following steps, use fine forceps or a perfect loop to transfer grids from one drop of solution to another, section side down. Use approximately 100-200 μl drops for MilliQ water, and 50-100 μl for uranyl acetate and lead citrate.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"c9a2h","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"64nto","text":"Stain sections with 0.6% filtered uranyl acetate in MilliQ water for 3 minutes.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"5fqv8","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"dq2nn","text":"Uranyl acetate enhances contrast of sections by interacting with proteins and lipids. The solution must be wrapped in foil and stored in a dark place to prevent precipitation from exposure to UV light.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"4vei9","text":"Rinse 5 x 1 min in MilliQ water.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"6em0p","text":"Stain sections with 0.1-0.4% filtered lead citrate in MilliQ water for 3 minutes. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"90cdl","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"d53m2","text":"Four drops of 10M sodium hydroxide should be added to the lead citrate stock solution prior to use to prevent lead citrate precipitating to form water-insoluble lead carbonate by exposure to carbon dioxide. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"1oqb6","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"fupad","text":"Lead citrate enhances contrast of sections by interacting with proteins and glycogens, and binding to osmium and uranyl acetate.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"e9iec","text":"Rinse 5 x 1 min in MilliQ water.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"2rmbf","text":"Place grids section side up on a sheet of filter paper, cover with a glass petri dish and dry for 10 minutes. Store grids in a grid storage box.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"blbit","text":"Place a grid in a transmission electron microscope grid holder for high resolution imaging using a transmission electron microscope.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"7i2n7","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"ge56","text":"Example: JEOL JEM-1400-Plus TEM at 80 keV equipped with a high sensitivity bottom mount CMOS 'Flash' camera.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
